data.description:
Country style living on acreage with 360-degree mountain views in Eckert on Colorado's Western Slope. This property is centrally located for recreation, shopping, scenic drives, wildlife viewings, small historic towns, and more. Hard to find 4.10 acres divided into 2 parcels each with an Orchard City water tap. Sectioned pastures, corrals, pond, irrigation water, well, barn with stalls,
loafing shed, tack storage and chicken coop make this a perfect setup for livestock and pets. One parcel has a 2400 sq ft, 3 bedroom, with bonus room, 2 ½ bath home. Gas fireplace in living area, chef's kitchen with granite counters, utility room, dining room, formal dining room, laundry room, 
 carpet/vinyl/tile flooring throughout, ceiling to floor windows, and skylights all in a
well-designed floor plan create the perfect flow for spacious living. French doors lead to a covered patio with a swim spa that is
included and a fenced backyard with gorgeous views. Oversized, detached 3 car garage, partly insulated with 220 power. The
second parcel has a storage shed and is ready for another home or keep it for an extra corral or pasture. Circle drive with mature shade trees, pine, shrubs and plenty of room for RV or trailer parking. Easy year-round access to Grand Mesa National Forest and all the recreation Colorado provides. A 3.7% VA loan is transferable to another Veteran that can qualify for this type of loan.
